Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Lightly oil a
#baking sheet{}. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄4-inch-thick rounds. Trim and mince
@scallions{2}(trimmed and minced, whites separated from greens). Peel and mince
@garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

== Potatoes ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss potatoes with @cooking oil{2%TBSP} and a couple big pinches of
@salt{} and @pepper{} until thoroughly coated.

Add potatoes to one side of prepared baking sheet in a single overlapping layer (for 4,
spread potatoes out across entire sheet). TIP: Be sure to shingle the potatoes in a
single layer so they cook evenly.

Roast on middle rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

== Meatloaves ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Bachan's Original Japanese Barbecue Sauce{1.75%ounce}
with @chili powder{1/2%tsp}. Taste and season with @salt{}.

In a second large bowl, soak @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} with @water{2%tsp} until water
has absorbed. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, scallion whites, garlic, @sweet and smoky BBQ
seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @chili powder{1/4%tsp}, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and a pinch of
@pepper{}.

TIP: Be sure to measure the chili powder; we sent more.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4). TIP: Wet hands or coat with oil
first to prevent sticking.

== Assembly ==

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss
green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}.

Place meatloaves next to green beans. Brush tops of meatloaves with 1 TBSP barbecue
glaze each (save the rest for later). (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting; add
meatloaves and green beans to a separate lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.)

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and green beans are tender and
browned, ~{15%minutes} (you'll finish glazing the meatloaves then).

== Scallion Crema ==

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} with
scallion greens to taste (we used half); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in
@water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Finishing ==

Once meatloaves and green beans have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven.
Transfer green beans to a #plate{}. Brush tops of meatloaves with remaining barbecue
glaze.

Return baking sheet to oven until meatloaves are cooked through and glaze is tacky,
~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide meatloaves, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle potatoes with
scallion crema and serve.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.